pageContext.claim: “And I came in, I had one hundred and forty eight openings. I said -- you're supposed to have none. I said 'How many do we have?' 'One hundred and forty eight.' I said, 'You've got to be kidding.'”
pageContext.analysis: Trump inherited 105 lifetime federal judicial vacancies requiring a presidential nomination when he was inaugurated on January 20, 2017. Almost no president comes into office with no vacancies.
